pageContext.claim: “They [China] are considered a developing nation. You see I have been sort of protesting that like but they are considering China -- as a developing nation you get all sorts of things that you would never get, advantages over the United States, but we have very strongly protested that. They are not a developing nation; they are a very powerful developed nation, and you know what, they have got to pay what everyone else has to pay.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is complaining about the World Trade Organization, which under its rules considers China a "developing" nation while the United States is deemed a "developed" nation. Although it has become an economic powerhouse, China is not classified as a developed nation because wages and GDP per-capita remain relatively low.
